<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,1016,1188]" box="[199,1286,1016,1044]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1016,1043]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,458,1017,1043]" name="Portugal" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: Baixo Alentejo (
<bibRefCitation author="Naglis, S. &amp; Bartak, M." box="[653,903,1016,1043]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="125 - 137" refId="ref33294" refString="Naglis, S. &amp; Bartak, M. (2015) Dolichopodidae (Diptera) from the Iberian Peninsula, with description of three new species. Zootaxa, 3964 (1), 125 - 137. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3964.1.9" type="journal article" year="2015">Naglis &amp; Barták 2015</bibRefCitation>
) and Algarve (Dyte unpubl. data).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,1016,1188]" box="[199,579,1053,1079]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,1053,1079]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Ecology.</emphasis>
Mainly on littoral rocks.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,1016,1188]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1089,1115]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Remarks.</emphasis>
Like 
<bibRefCitation author="Naglis, S. &amp; Bartak, M." box="[332,597,1088,1115]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="125 - 137" refId="ref33294" refString="Naglis, S. &amp; Bartak, M. (2015) Dolichopodidae (Diptera) from the Iberian Peninsula, with description of three new species. Zootaxa, 3964 (1), 125 - 137. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3964.1.9" type="journal article" year="2015">Naglis &amp; Barták (2015)</bibRefCitation>
our survey also produced one single female specimen that might belong to this species, but we decided to treat it as 
<emphasis box="[617,799,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">doubtful species</emphasis>
as differences were noticed with females of this species from northern 
<collectingCountry box="[314,390,1161,1187]" name="France" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">France</collectingCountry>
(where they were found associated with males).
</paragraph>
